insider.com%2F657c375c50edbc52a864a249%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepsouth-supercomputer-simulates-human-brain-go-online-next-year-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20supercomputer%2C%20named%20DeepSouth%2C%20will%20be%20capable%20of%20228%20trillion%20synaptic%20operations%20a%20second%2C%20rivalling%20operations%20of%20the%20human%20brain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ezolfagharifard%40insider.com%20(Ellie%20Zolfagharifard)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepsouth-supercomputer-simulates-human-brain-go-online-next-year-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20told%20I%20was%20'selfish'%20for%20being%20single%20at%2038.%20But%20I%20needed%20those%20years%20of%20independence.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20smiling%20and%20staring%20at%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b772a50edbc52a8647754%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222890%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20reading%20comments%20on%20a%20recent%20essay%20I%20wrote%2C%20I%20spent%20some%20time%20reflecting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%2038%2C%20I've%20realized%20I'm%20now%20ready%20to%20find%20a%20partner%20and%20have%20a%20child%2C%20and%20people%20called%20me%20selfish.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20comments%20bothered%20me%20at%20first%2C%20but%20I%20thought%20about%20what%20it%20actually%20means%20to%20be%20selfish.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%20I%20wrote%20an%20essay%20about%20a%20recent%20realization.%20After%20my%20eight-year%20marriage%20in%20my%2020s%20(when%20I%20was%20career-focused%20and%20uninterested%20in%20motherhood)%20and%20divorce%2C%20then%20another%20wonderful%20but%20aimless%20seven-year%20relationship%20in%20my%2030s%2C%20I'm%20now%2038%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsingle-childless-want-husband-family-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eready%20for%20a%20husband%20and%20child%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20my%20article%20was%20published%20on%20Business%20Insider%2C%20it%20began%20trending%20on%20Yahoo%20and%20MSN.%20My%20story%20had%20tons%20of%20comments%2C%20and%20I%20received%20numerous%20notifications%2C%20messages%2C%20and%20connection%20requests%20on%20every%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20made%20it!%26quot%3B%20I%20thought.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20be%20hocking%20a%20lip%20kit%20in%20no%20time!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20seriousness%2C%20I%20was%20shocked%20by%20the%20attention%20my%20writing%20was%20getting.%20I%20felt%20like%20just%20another%20woman%20sharing%20a%20story%20about%20approaching%2040%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnever-had-the-urge-have-children-im-childless-and-happy-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20a%20husband%20and%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20think%20my%20story%20was%20terribly%20original.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20shocked%20by%20some%20of%20the%20comments%20and%20messages%20I%20got%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20I%20sifted%20through%20over%201.5k%20comments%20on%20the%20websites%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20numerous%20emails%20and%20direct%20messages%2C%20sent%20straight%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%20I%20realized%20men%2C%20particularly%2C%20were%20infuriated%20by%20what%20I%20had%20written.%20They%20said%20I%20had%20%26quot%3Bhit%20the%20wall%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20I'd%20gotten%20what%20I%20deserved%20for%20being%20selfish%2C%20career-obsessed%2C%20and%20not%20wanting%20children%20during%20my%20marriage.%20There%20were%20also%20suggestions%20that%20I%20seek%20a%20therapist.%20I%20have%20one%2C%20thank%20you%20very%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsingle-no-kids-woman-viral-received-abuse-online-interview-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincredible%20vitriol%20leveled%20at%20me%20through%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20my%20essay%2C%20I%20was%20feeling%20pretty%20defensive%20in%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20this%20writing.%20Remarks%20like%20%26quot%3BToo%20selfish%20to%20be%20a%20mother%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdo%20somebody%20a%20favor%20and%20stay%20single%26quot%3B%20(and%20those%20are%20the%20nicer%20ones!)%20felt%20like%20personal%20attacks%20on%20my%20character.%20I%20wanted%20to%20justify%20and%20defend%20myself.%20However%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20different%2C%20more%20progressive%20approach%20to%20my%20critics.%20Rather%20than%20searching%20for%20all%20the%20things%20these%20commenters%20were%20saying%20that%20weren't%20true%2C%20I%20asked%20myself%20what%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20was%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20word%20I%20read%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%20again%20that%20I%20felt%20forced%20to%20confront%20%E2%80%94%20selfish.%20I've%20never%20viewed%20myself%20as%20a%20particularly%20selfish%20person%2C%20but%20as%20I%20continued%20to%20think%20about%20what%20that%20word%20actually%20means%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20chiefly%20concerned%20with%20oneself%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20it%20began%20to%20resonate%20with%20me%20and%20how%20I've%20lived%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBeing%20selfish%20isn't%20always%20a%20bad%20thing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20the%20type%20of%20person%20who%20would%20rather%20go%20out%20alone%20than%20go%20to%20the%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20my%20friends%20like.%20I%20hate%20carpooling%20because%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20listen%20to%20other%20people's%20music%20and%20want%20to%20come%20and%20go%20as%20I%20please.%20I%20won't%20sacrifice%20my%20time%20or%20money%20doing%20things%20I%20don't%20like%20or%20being%20around%20people%20I%20don't%20care%20for%2C%20even%20when%20it's%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%20I%20don't%20even%20travel%20with%20other%20people%20unless%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20do%20what%20I%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20right%2C%20guys.%20While%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20always%20wrong%2C%20I%20am%20selfish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(But%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20look%2050!%20That%20one%20was%20a%20low%20blow%20from%20a%20commenter%20who%20shall%20not%20be%20named.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Freasons-youre-better-off-being-single-according-to-science-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunwilling%20to%20live%20for%20more%20than%20myself%20%3C%2Fa%3Euntil%20this%20point%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20did%20not%20want%20to%20put%20my%20husband's%20or%20potential%20children's%20needs%20above%20my%20own%20when%20I%20was%20married%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20and%20I%20chose%20a%20relationship%20in%20my%2030s%20that%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20continue%20to%20pursue%20the%20things%20I%20wanted.%20Quite%20frankly%2C%20though%20it%20has%20become%20much%20more%20appealing%20to%20me%2C%20the%20thought%20of%20giving%20up%20everything%20I%20do%20for%20myself%20to%20care%20for%20others%20is%20still%20scary.%20Marriage%20and%20children%20are%20about%20sacrifice.%20I%20was%20not%20prepared%20for%2C%20nor%20did%20I%20trust%20myself%20to%20be%20that%20person%20until%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20judgment%20has%20been%20directed%20at%20my%20%26quot%3Bme%26quot%3B-focused%20life%2C%20had%20I%20not%20indulged%20in%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-being-single-is-good-for-your-self-esteem-and-confidence-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eself-centered%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I%20would%20be%20confident%20about%20the%20idea%20of%20devoting%20my%20future%20to%20a%20hypothetical%20husband%20and%20children%2C%20should%20I%20meet%20the%20right%20person%20to%20start%20a%20family%20with.%20Though%20I've%20enjoyed%20being%20selfish%20up%20until%20this%20point%2C%20I've%20started%20to%20feel%20that%20kind%20of%20life%20lacks%20meaning%20and%20purpose%20for%20me%2C%20and%20it's%20that%20feeling%20that's%20given%20me%20incredible%20clarity%20about%20my%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20taken%20me%2038%20years%20to%20get%20to%20this%20place%2C%20and%20perhaps%20some%20people%20think%20it%20was%20wrong%20of%20me%20to%20let%20my%20selfish%20desires%20keep%20me%20from%20having%20the%20family%20I%20could%20have%20had%20earlier%20in%20life%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20%E2%80%94%20and%20can't%20%E2%80%94%20go%20back%20and%20do%20things%20differently.%20I%20was%20not%20the%20person%20I've%20grown%20into%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20was%20ready%20for%20the%20commitment%20and%20responsibility%20of%20a%20family%20until%20now.%20All%20I%20can%20do%20moving%20forward%20is%20set%20aside%20my%20own%20wants%20and%20prepare%20myself%20for%20a%20husband%20(who%20%26quot%3Bwould%20have%20to%20be%20crazy%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20with%20me%2C%20according%20to%20commenters)%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20I%20told%20myself%20I'd%20refrain%20from%20being%20defensive%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20address%20one%20particularly%20hurtful%20and%20untrue%20comment.%20%26quot%3BPlucking%20the%20eyebrows%20%26amp%3B%20drawing%20them%20on%20the%20forehead%20doesn't%20help%20her%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20read.%20I'll%20have%20you%20know%20those%20are%20my%20natural%20eyebrows%2C%20sir!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-woman-years-called-selfish-independence-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702642261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b774a0ec98e92f74fb281%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-woman-years-called-selfish-independence-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20wro