ges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20judge%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Duke%20of%20Sussex%20in%2015%20of%20the%2033%20sample%20articles%20that%20he%20submitted%20as%20evidence%20in%20his%20lawsuit%20against%20MGN%2C%20which%20publishes%20The%20Mirror%2C%20Sunday%20Mirror%2C%20and%20Sunday%20People.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Timothy%20Fancourt%20said%20he%20had%20concluded%20that%20the%20newspapers%20carried%20out%20%26quot%3Bextensive%26quot%3B%20phone%20hacking%20of%20celebrities%20between%202006%20and%202011%2C%20even%20when%20a%20public%20inquiry%20into%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20British%20press%20was%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20consider%20that%20his%20phone%20was%20only%20hacked%20to%20a%20modest%20extent%2C%20and%20that%20this%20was%20probably%20carefully%20controlled%20by%20certain%20people%20at%20each%20newspaper%2C%26quot%3B%20Fancourt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrince%20Harry%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20read%20outside%20court%20by%20his%20lawyer%20that%20the%20ruling%20was%20%26quot%3Bvindicating%20and%20affirming%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20MGN%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWhere%20historical%20wrongdoing%20took%20place%2C%20we%20apologise%20unreservedly%2C%20have%20taken%20full%20responsibility%20and%20paid%20appropriate%20compensation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%2C%20the%20younger%20son%20of%20King%20Charles%20III%2C%20became%20the%20first%20British%20royal%20in%20over%20a%20century%20to%20take%20to%20the%20witness%20stand%20when%20he%20gave%20evidence%20in%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20a%20royal%20had%20given%20evidence%20in%20court%20was%20in%20the%201890s%2C%20when%20the%20future%20king%20Edward%20VII%20took%20the%20stand%20in%20a%20slander%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%2C%2039%2C%20accused%20the%20publisher%20of%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20scale%26quot%3B%20phone%20hacking%20during%20emotional%20testimony%20in%20which%20he%20relived%20upsetting%20episodes%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20he%20had%20been%20the%20victim%20of%20relentless%20and%20distressing%20media%20intrusion%20virtually%20his%20entire%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prince%20and%20several%20other%20claimants%20alleged%20the%20titles%20engaged%20in%20%26quot%3Billegal%20information%20gathering%26quot%3B%2C%20including%20intercepting%20phone%20voice%20mails%2C%20to%20write%20dozens%20of%20stories%20about%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiana's%20death%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Duke%20of%20Sussex%2C%20as%20he%20is%20also%20known%2C%20has%20launched%20legal%20action%20against%20several%20tabloid%20media%20groups%2C%20alongside%20barrages%20of%20attacks%20aimed%20at%20his%20family%20and%20the%20monarchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20told%20that%20slaying%20dragons%20will%20get%20you%20burned%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20his%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20in%20light%20of%20today's%20victory%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20doing%20what%20is%20needed%20for%20a%20free%20and%20honest%20press%20it's%20a%20worthwhile%20price%20to%20pay.%20The%20mission%20continues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMGN%20had%20admitted%20to%20%26quot%3Bsome%20evidence%26quot%3B%20of%20unlawful%20information%20gathering%2C%20including%20for%20a%20story%20about%20Harry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20had%20denied%20voicemail%20interception%20and%20also%20argued%20that%20some%20claims%20were%20brought%20too%20late%20by%20Harry%20and%20the%20other%20claimants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarry%20has%20long%20had%20a%20turbulent%20relationship%20with%20the%20press%20and%20holds%20the%20media%20responsible%20for%20the%20death%20of%20his%20mother%2C%20Princess%20Diana%2C%20in%20a%201997%20Paris%20car%20crash%20while%20being%20pursued%20by%20paparazzi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAllegations%20that%20tabloid%20journalists%20hacked%20into%20celebrities'%20phones%20first%20emerged%20two%20decades%20ago%20