ent%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2012%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frajya-sabha-passes-bill-election-commissioners-opposition-appointment%5C%22%3Eapproved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%2C%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill.%20This%20legislation%20replaces%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(Conditions%20of%20Service%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20Transaction%20of%20Business)%20Act%2C%201991.%20The%20primary%20objective%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20to%20govern%20the%20appointment%2C%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20and%20tenure%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(ECs)%2C%20and%20to%20establish%20procedures%20for%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20will%20be%20composed%20of%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs.%20The%20number%20of%20ECs%20will%20be%20determined%20periodically%20by%20the%20President.%20The%20appointment%20of%20the%20Commission%20will%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President%20based%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20consists%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20(or%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20minister%20will%20head%20a%20Search%20Committee%20tasked%20with%20proposing%20five%20names%20to%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%20Notably%2C%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20also%20holds%20the%20authority%20to%20consider%20individuals%20beyond%20those%20suggested%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20selection%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20under%20Article%20324%20is%20contingent%20upon%20legislation%20enacted%20by%20Parliament.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fcases%2Fanoop-baranwal-v-union-of-india-election-commission-appointments-background%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAnoop%20Baranwal%20v%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20emphasised%20that%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20intended%20to%20establish%20an%20independent%20Election%20Commission%20with%20appointments%20governed%20by%20law%2C%20not%20subject%20to%20executive%20discretion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20ruled%20that%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20specific%20legislation%20from%20Parliament%2C%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20would%20be%20contingent%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20a%20Selection%20Committee.%20As%20per%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20vision%2C%20this%20Committee%20would%20comprise%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20(or%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20opposition%20party).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20current%20Bill%20raises%20concerns%20as%20it%20modifies%20this%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20negates%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20one%20cabinet%20minister%20is%20included%20in%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20is%20predominantly%20composed%20of%20members%20from%20the%20ruling%20government%2C%20potentially%20jeopardising%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20members%20recognised%20the%20importance%20of%20entrusting%20the%20responsibility%20of%20conducting%20elections%20to%20individuals%20free%20from%20political%20influences%20and%20local%20pressures.%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20emphasised%20that%20true%20electoral%20freedom%20required%20distancing%20elections%20from%20the%20control%20of%20the%20ruling%20government.%20Both%20the%20Goswami%20report%20of%201990%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%20report%20of%202015%20specified%20that%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20should%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3EElection%20Commissioners%E2%80%99%20Appointment%20Bill%3A%20Farewell%20to%20Free%20and%20Fair%20Elections%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20limitations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20proposed%20Bill%2C%20only%20individuals%20who%20currently%20hold%20or%20have%20held%20a%20position%20equivalent%20to%20the%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20are%20deemed%20eligible%20for%20the%20roles%20of%20CEC%20or%20ECs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20their%20administrative%20functions%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20also%20functions%20in%20a%20quasi-judicial%20capacity%2C%20making%20determinations%20on%20matters%20such%20as%20the%20disqualification%20of%20Members%20of%20Parliament%20and%20State%20Legislatures%2C%20as%20well%20as%20adjudicating%20disputes%20related%20to%20symbol%20allocation%20and%20the%20registration%20of%20political%20parties.%20The%20limitation%20of%20eligibility%20criteria%20to%20civil%20servants%20under%20the%20Bill%20raises%20concerns%20as%20it%20may%20exclude%20qualified%20individuals%20from%20diverse%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComparatively%2C%20examining%20the%20composition%20of%20Election%20Commissions%20in%20other%20countries%20reveals%20a%20broader%20eligibility%20criteria.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20appointees%20must%20not%20be%20currently%20elected%20or%20appointed%20officers%2C%20nor%20hold%20federal%20government%20positions%20in%20the%20executive%2C%20legislative%2C%20or%20judicial%20branches%20at%20the%20time%20of%20their%20appointment.%20In%20South%20Africa%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20a%20five-member%20body%2C%20with%20one%20member%20required%20to%20be%20a%20judge.%20All%20members%20must%20be%20South%20African%20citizens%20without%20prominent%20party-political%20affiliations.%20This%20highlights%20a%20more%20inclusive%20approach%20to%20eligibility%20in%20other%20countries%E2%80%99%20electoral%20bodies%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20more%20restrictive%20criteria%20proposed%20by%20the%20current%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20affirms%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20even%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20vacancy%20or%20an%20issue%20in%20its%20constitution.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20a%20vacancy%20in%20this%20Committee%20can%20only%20occur%20under%20specific%20circumstances.%20Among%20the%20three%20Committee%20members%2C%20the%20positions%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20a%20cabinet%20minister%20are%20inherently%20secure%20and%20cannot%20be%20vacant.%20The%20only%20potential%20vacancy%20could%20be%20in%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20which%20may%20arise%20if%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20dissolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20a%20vacancy%20may%20only%20occur%20before%20a%20general%20election%2C%20and%20during%20such%20a%20period%2C%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20would%20exclusively%20comprise%20members%20from%20the%20ruling%20party.%20This%20scenario%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20potential%20lack%20of%20opposition%20representation%20in%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20during%20crucial%20decision-making%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20Bill%20neglects%20to%20address%20persistent%20issues%20that%20have%20plagued%20the%20Election%20Commission%20over%20the%20years.%20Notably%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20to%20recognise%20that%20no%20CEC%20has%20successfully%20completed%20a%20full%20six-year%20term%20since%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinancial%20matters%20concerning%20the%20Election%20Commission%20are%20subject%20to%20government%20control%2C%20with%20the%20funds%20not%20being%20drawn%20from%20the%20consolidated%20fund%20of%20India.%20This%20arrangement%20implies%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20wields%20significant%20power%20and%20authority%20over%20the%20finances%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20lacks%20an%20independent%20staff%2C%20relying%20on%20personnel%20from%20both%20central%20and%20state%20governments%20whenever%20elections%20are%20conducted.%20In%20essence%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20operates%20as%20a%20largely%20powerless%20entity%2C%20as%20it%20lacks%20the%20ability%20to%20enforce%20inner-party%20democracy%20or%20regulate%20party%20finances.%20These%20shortcomings%20underscore%20the%20need%20for%20comprehensive%20reforms%20that%20go%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20current%20Bill%20in%20order%20to%20address%20the%20systemic%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20overlooked%20the%20private%20member%20Bill%20presented%20by%20MP%20Manish%20Tewari%2C%20which%20purportedly%20contained%20solutions%20to%20the%20existing%20problems%20within%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20The%20Bill%20argued%20that%20the%20internal%20structures%20and%20functioning%20of%20numerous%20political%20parties%20had%20become%20excessively%20opaque%20and%20rigid%2C%20emphasising%20the%20necessity%20to%20make%20their%20operations%20transparent%2C%20accountable%2C%20and%20rule-based.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20envisioned%20Selection%20Committee%20in%20the%20Bill%20included%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20as%20the%20chairman%2C%20alongside%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20two%20most%20senior%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20its%20members.%20This%20proposed%20committee%20aimed%20to%20bring%20a%20more%20inclusive%20and%20diverse%20approach%20to%20the%20decision-making%20process%20regarding%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20structure%20and%20functioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20proposed%20that%20the%20regulation%2C%20monitoring%20and%20superintendence%20of%20internal%20functioning%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%20internal%20election%20of%20all%20registered%20political%20parties%20under%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20shall%20be%20vested%20in%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20further%20said%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20shall%20regulate%2C%20monitor%20and%20superintend%20the%20internal%20election%20of%20registered%20political%20parties%20in%20accordance%20with%20their%20respective%20constitutions%20until%20a%20Model%20Internal%20Code%20is%20prescribed%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20suggested%20alterations%20could%20potentially%20impact%20the%20autonomy%20and%20operations%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20.%20The%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20paramount%20to%20guarantee%20impartiality%20and%20integrity%20in%20the%20execution%20of%20electoral%20processes.%20Any%20perceived%20influence%20of%20the%20Executive%20in%20the%20selection%20process%20may%20give%20rise%20to%20apprehensions%20regarding%20the%20EC%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20fulfil%20its%20duties%20without%20prejudice.%20Upholding%20the%20non-partisan%20nature%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20essential%20for%20maintaining%20public%20trust%20in%20the%20electoral%20system%20and%20ensuring%20fair%20and%20unbiased%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBhuvnesh%20Kumar%20and%20Sharad%20Panwar%20are%20fourth%20year%20law%20students%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Jodhpur.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702638005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-are-the-unseen-effects-of-the-election-commissioner-bill-on-electoral-governance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Any%20perceived%20influence%20of%20the%20Executive%20in%20the%20selection%20process%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20may%20give%20rise%20to%20apprehensions%20regarding%20the%20Election%20Commission's%20capacity%20to%20fulfil%20its%20duties%20without%20prejudice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-are-the-unseen-effects-of-the-election-commissioner-bill-on-electoral-governance%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lyft%20President%20Kristin%26nbsp%3BSverchek%20on%202024%3A%20'I'm%20excited%20to%20just%20move%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20a%20bias%20towards%20action.'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22910%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kristin%20Sverchek.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b6e5c7a3c8094d5dd324e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKristin%20Sverchek.%3Cp%3ELyft%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELyft%20President%C2%A0Kristin%C2%A0Sverchek%20is%20full%20of%20optimism%20for%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20excited%20to%20just%20move%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20a%20bias%20to%20action%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESverchek's%20insights%20are%20part%20of%20Business%20Insider's%20year-end%20leadership%20series%2C%20%26quot%3BLooking%20Ahead%202024.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2011%20years%20at%20Lyft%2C%20Kristin%C2%A0Sverchek%20stepped%20into%20the%20president's%20role%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20the%20ride-hailing%20company's%20first%20general%20counsel%2C%20helped%20take%20Lyft%20public%2C%20and%20was%20named%20president%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20gotten%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flyft-president-career-advice-women-in-workplace-taylor-swift-song-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomfortable%20using%20her%20voice%20over%20the%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20certain%20leadership%20muscles%20being%20%26quot%3Bhard%20to%20develop%2C%26quot%3B%20Sverchek%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20working%20in%20male-dominated%20fields%20of%20tech%20and%20law%20isn't%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20grit%20and%20resilience%20and%20it%20took%20me%20challenging%20myself%20to%20speak%20up%20even%20when%20I%20didn't%20feel%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20Sverchek%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20sort%20of%20thing%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20say%20to%20each%20other%2C%20which%20is%20like%20'If%20I%20were%20a%20man%2C%20how%20would%20I%20handle%20this%3F'%20And%20so%20sometimes%20it%20helps%20me%20to%20apply%20that%20rubric%20to%20a%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESverchek's%20insights%20are%20part%20of%20Business%20Insider's%20year-end%20leadership%20package%2C%20%26quot%3BLooking%20Ahead%202024%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20digs%20into%20vision%2C%20strategy%2C%20and%20challenges%20across%20corporate%20America.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20you%20looking%20forward%20to%20most%20for%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I'm%20really%20excited%20about%20is%20that%20right%20now%20it's%20feeling%20like%20we%20have%20a