ide%20India.%20Go%20over%20there.%20We%20are%20not%20going%20to%20have%20an%20adjudication%20over%20here.%20The%20person%20detained%20has%20not%20given%20the%20affidavit.%20If%20there%20is%20violation%20of%20any%20law%20etc%20you%20have%20to%20go%20to%20court%20over%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20C.%20Aryama%20Sundaram%2C%20appearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioner%2C%20said%20that%20the%20plea%20has%20been%20filed%20by%20a%20family%20member%20of%20Gupta%E2%80%99s.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fplea-in-supreme-court-seeks-consular-assistance-to-indian-detained-in-czech-over-gurpatwant-singh-pannun-murder-plot-244610%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Sundaram%20argued%20that%20he%20is%20only%20pressing%20the%20relief%20for%20adequate%20consular%20assistance.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20an%20extremely%20sensitive%20matter%20for%20any%20Ministry%20to%20come%20in.%20It%E2%80%99s%20for%20them%20to%20decide%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESundaram%20has%20also%20asked%20for%20an%20in-chamber%20hearing%2C%20and%20Justice%20Khanna%20said%20the%20request%20would%20be%20considered%20at%20the%20next%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20claims%20that%20Gupta%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cillegally%20detained%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20circumstances%20surrounding%20his%20arrest%20were%20marked%20by%20irregularities%2C%20with%20no%20formal%20arrest%20warrant%20presented%2C%20and%20the%20apprehension%20executed%20by%20self-claimed%20US%20agents%20rather%20than%20local%20Czech%20authorities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20plea%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20also%20claimed%20that%20Gupta%20is%20a%20devout%20Hindu%20and%20a%20vegetarian%2C%20but%20was%20%E2%80%9Cforced%20to%20consume%20beef%20and%20pork%E2%80%9D%20while%20in%20custody%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic%2C%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20He%20also%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20denied%20consular%20access%2C%20the%20right%20to%20contact%20his%20family%20in%20India%2C%20and%20the%20freedom%20to%20seek%20legal%20representation.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnikhil-gupta-pannun-plot-challenges-extradition-order-czech-court%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20Devirupa%20Mitra%20had%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Gupta%20had%20appealed%20a%20Prague%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20allowing%20his%20extradition%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2029%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20announced%20that%20they%20had%20charged%20Gupta%20with%20%E2%80%98murder%20for%20hire%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98conspiracy%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20ultimately%20failed%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Sikh%20activist%20in%20New%20York.%20The%20filed%20charges%20accused%20an%20unnamed%20but%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20Indian%20government%20official%E2%80%9D%20of%20recruiting%20Gupta%20to%20hire%20a%20%E2%80%98hitman%E2%80%99.%20The%20%E2%80%98hitman%E2%80%99%20that%20Gupta%20thought%20he%20was%20hiring%20was%20actually%20an%20undercover%20US%20law%20enforcement%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20target%20was%20also%20unnamed%20in%20the%20court%20documents%20but%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FMcOUf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eidentified%20by%20media%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20general%20counsel%20for%20the%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20a%20Khalistan%20advocacy%20group%20that%20is%20proscribed%20in%20India.%20Pannun%20is%20a%20US%20citizen%20who%20also%20holds%20Canadian%20nationality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGupta%20was%20arrested%20in%20Prague%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20US%20authorities%20when%20he%20arrived%20there%20from%20India%20on%20June%2030%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Czech%20ministry%20of%20justice%20spokesperson%20Vladimir%20%C5%98epka%C2%A0told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20had%20issued%20an%20order%20on%20November%2023%20on%20the%20admissibility%20of%20the%20extradition%20order%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20legal%20force.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20for%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20delay%20in%20implementing%20the%20order%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Gupta%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20(i.e.%20an%20ordinary%20remedy)%20against%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20on%20the%20admissibility%20of%20extradition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20would%20be%20a%20referral%20to%20the%20high%20court%20for%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20complaint%20by%20Gupta.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20high%20court%20in%20Prague%20shall%20either%20dismiss%20the%20complaint%20and%20thus%20uphold%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%2C%20revoke%20the%20challenged%20decision%20and%20refer%20the%20case%20back%20to%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20for%20a%20new%20hearing%2C%20or%20change%20the%20decision%20and%20rule%20on%20the%20inadmissibility%20of%20the%20extradition%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Repka.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702631433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25123828%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_03.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnikhil-gupta-approaches-indian-supreme-court-against-arrest-extradition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20petition%20claims%20that%20Gupta%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Billegally%20detained%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnikhil-gupta-approaches-indian-supreme-court-against-arrest-extradition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%