2%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22COP28%20Floundered%20on%20Fossil%20Fuels%2C%20Coal%20and%20Finance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15140054%2FGBNy-spXEAA_v-G.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20stark%20geopolitical%20tensions%20which%20have%20become%20characteristic%20of%20international%20summits%20lately%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20global%20climate%20conference%20COP28%20witnessed%20sharper%20differences%20between%20the%20%E2%80%98Like%20Minded%20Developing%20Countries%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20and%20the%20developed%20countries%20of%20the%20Global%20North.%20After%20the%20final%20day%20(December%2012)%20of%20the%20two-week%20COP28%20climate%20summit%20in%20Dubai%20saw%20a%20stalemate%20over%20the%20draft%20agreement%2C%20representatives%20continued%20negotiations%20to%20finally%20arrive%20at%20what%20is%20clearly%20now%20a%20compromised%20consensus%2C%20with%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%98unambitious%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98incremental%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98menu%E2%80%99%20and%20of%20%E2%80%98half%20measures%E2%80%99%20being%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20final%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F4821425d-d54b-411b-b48b-156005a5311f%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F4821425d-d54b-411b-b48b-156005a5311f%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702714281336000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2V6o4xsd9yZ-BCQp_Mh-ZM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edraft%20presented%20by%20COP28%20President%2C%20UAE%E2%80%99s%20Sultan%20al-Jaber%3C%2Fa%3E%20proposed%20eight%20options%20that%20countries%20could%20use%20to%20cut%20emissions%2C%20including%3A%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20both%20consumption%20and%20production%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20in%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%2C%20before%2C%20or%20around%202050%E2%80%9D%2C%20falling%20short%20of%20referring%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cphase%20out%E2%80%9D%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20It%20included%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20by%202030%2C%20%E2%80%9Crapidly%20phasing%20down%20unabated%20coal%E2%80%9D%20and%20scaling%20up%20technologies%20including%20those%20to%20capture%20CO2%20emissions%20to%20keep%20them%20from%20the%20atmosphere.%20The%20US%2C%20UK%20and%20EU%20led%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20countries%20to%20oppose%20the%20draft%20agreement%20which%20mentions%20the%20need%20to%20reduce%20emissions%20but%20did%20not%20outrightly%20state%20that%20fossil%20fuels%20should%20be%20phased%20out.%20Representatives%20for%20smaller%20Island%20Nations%20called%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeath%20sentence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20deal%20now%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9Ctransitioning%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20energy%20systems%2C%20in%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%20%E2%80%A6%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%202050%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20science%2C%E2%80%9D%20dropping%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cphasing%20away%E2%80%9D%20and%20including%20%E2%80%9Cfossil%20fuel.%E2%80%9D%20The%20agreement%20further%20calls%20for%20phasing%20out%20inefficient%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20and%20for%20%E2%80%9Caccelerating%20phase%20down%E2%80%9D%20of%20coal%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20developing%20nations%20along%20with%20major%20oil%20producers%20are%20opposed%20to%20any%20demand%20for%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20the%20point%20that%20India%20had%20been%20making%20throughout%20the%20discussions%20is%20that%20the%20focus%20needs%20to%20move%20away%20from%20coal%20because%20the%20science%20very%20clearly%20states%20that%20it%20is%20a%20carbon%20emission%20problem%20and%20all%20the%20fossil%20fuels%20need%20to%20be%20targeted.%20Although%20the%20discussions%20failed%20to%20feature%20accountability%20for%20historic%20polluters%2C%20in%20his%20speech%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F03336eaa-d80b-4b11-8f01-9b59e34dfdde%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F03336eaa-d80b-4b11-8f01-9b59e34dfdde%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702714281336000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0CjTLS6pxrxuek3cs8cqM2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%E2%80%9Crebuked%E2%80%9D%20large%20emitters%20like%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20releasing%20the%20most%20climate-warming%20emissions%20since%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20at%20COP28%2C%20%E2%80%9COver%20the%20past%20century%2C%20a%20small%20section%20of%20humanity%20has%20indiscriminately%20exploited%20nature.%20However%2C%20entire%20humanity%20is%20paying%20the%20price%20for%20this%2C%20especially%20people%20living%20in%20the%20Global%20South.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exclusive%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%98rapidly%20phasing%20down%20coal%E2%80%99%20drew%20exception%20from%20India%2C%20and%20it%20was%20joined%20by%20China%20in%20abstaining%20from%20signing%20the%20Global%20Renewables%20and%20Energy%20Efficiency%20Pledge%20aimed%20at%20tripling%20installed%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20by%202030.%20Despite%20finding%20mention%20at%20the%20G20%20declaration%20in%20September%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20not%20sign%20the%20COP28%20global%20pledge%20was%20likely%20related%20to%20the%20framing%20of%20the%20text%20specifically%20around%20the%20severe%20stance%20on%20phasing%20out%20coal.%20India%20has%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20phasing%20in%20renewables%2C%20and%20upholds%20that%20tripling%20of%20renewable%20energy%20and%20doubling%20of%20energy%20efficiency%20must%20not%20be%20covered%20with%20the%20phasing%20out%20of%20coal.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20nationally%20determined%20contributions%20(NDCs)%2C%20it%20has%20already%20committed%20to%20installing%20500%20GW%20of%20electricity%20from%20non-fossil%20fuel%20sources%20by%202030.%20Between%202017-23%2C%20India%20added%20100%20GW%20of%20installed%20electric%20capacity%2C%20of%20which%2080%25%20was%20from%20renewable%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20coal%E2%80%99s%20days%20are%20not%20over%20in%20India.%20Despite%20setting%20out%20some%20of%20the%20most%20aggressive%20renewable%20energy%20targets%20in%20the%20world%2C%20coal%20remains%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20urban%20industrial%20development%20projects%2C%20and%20a%20major%20source%20of%20jobs.%20It%20is%20important%20for%20the%20Global%20North%20to%20appreciate%20what%20transition%20from%20coal%20means%20for%20poor%20countries%20like%20India.%20Just%20consider%20the%20coal%20supply%20chains%2C%20taking%20India%20as%20a%20typical%20country%20of%20the%20global%20South.%20From%20the%20pitheads%2C%20coal%20is%20brought%20by%20trucks%20to%20a%20nearby%20cold%20depot%20from%20where%20it%20is%20transported%20again%20by%20trucks%20to%20the%20nearest%20railway%20station.%20Truck%20driving%20is%20the%20profession%20of%20choice%20for%20many%20poor%20migrants%20from%20rural%20areas%20and%20there%20are%20some%20two%20million%20registered%20on%20Indian%20roads.%20By%20a%20conservative%20estimate%2C%20at%20least%20a%20quarter%20of%20this%20carries%20coal.%20Each%20truck%20has%20a%20driver%20and%20two%20helpers%20who%20have%20families%2C%20which%20means%20that%201.5%20million%20are%20reliant%20on%20just%20coal%20trucking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupply%20chain%20disruptions%20due%20to%20developments%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20slowed%20down%20the%20momentum%20in%20transitioning%20to%20renewable%20energy%20options%2C%20everywhere.%20Upgrades%20for%20electricity%20storage%20require%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20and%20transmission%20systems%20are%20built%20for%20coal%20and%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20which%20means%20they%20will%20need%20significant%20technology%20advancement%20for%20renewables.%20Nuclear%20and%20hydropower%20are%20considered%20essential%20to%20energy%20transitions%2C%20but%20globally%20there%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fefad627c-f556-4bc1-9291-5b98b45c0065%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fefad627c-f556-4bc1-9291-5b98b45c0065%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702714281336000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0-eLIT0ohMR3JVRdEGMYMx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20disagreement%20over%20whether%20large%20dams%20are%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20renewable%20energy%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommitments%20made%20around%20climate%20finance%20at%20COP28%20remain%20weak%2C%20and%20although%20a%20%24700%20million%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund%20has%20been%20approved%2C%20it%20falls%20way%20below%20the%20estimated%20%24400%20billion%20needed%20to%20effectively%20begin%20addressing%20climate%20change.%20Technology%20transfers%20have%20been%20spoken%20of%20at%20COP28%3B%20but%20how%20much%20of%20this%20will%20actually%20transpire%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20The%20developed%20world%20retains%20its%20significant%20representation%20in%20deciding%20where%20funds%20go.%20Without%20financial%20backing%2C%20developing%20nations%20cannot%20think%20of%20ambitious%20action%20on%20mitigations.%20Sustainable%20finance%20instruments%20and%20technology%20transfer%20remain%20critical%20to%20building%20expensive%20projects%20that%20can%20effectively%20address%20climate%20change.%20The%20nature%20of%20finance%20flows%20needs%20to%20be%20demystified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20must%20insist%20that%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%20must%20be%20differentiated%20depending%20on%20national%20circumstances%20and%20on%20a%20time%20scale%2C%20and%20technology%20transfer%2C%20co-development%20and%20access%20form%20the%20core%20of%20the%20energy%20transition.%20The%20COP28%20Dubai%20agreement%20may%20have%20created%20optics%20of%20convergence%20between%20the%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries%2C%20but%20there%20will%20be%20massive%20dissonance%20over%20how%20differentiated%20responsibility%20will%20be%20worked%20out%20in%20determining%20the%20absolute%20reduction%20of%20emissions%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVaishali%20Basu%20Sharma%20is%20a%20strategic%20and%20economic%20affairs%20analyst.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702630835000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15140054%2FGBNy-spXEAA_v-G.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-floundered-fossil-fuels-coal-finance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20must%20insist%20that%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%20must%20be%20differentiated%20depending%20on%20national%20circumstances%20and%20on%20a%20time%20scale%2C%20and%20technology%20transfer%2C%20co-development%20and%20access%20form%20the%20core%20of%20the%20energy%20transition.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-floundered-fossil-fuels-coal-finance%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Go%20Air%20Troubles%20Mount%20As%20Billionaire%20Backed%20Airline%20Nears%20Shut%20Down%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAnother%20airline%20backed%20by%20a%20billionaire%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20shutting%20down%20for%20good%2C%20having%20tried%20and%20so%20far%20failed%20to%20attract%20a%20savior%20after%20entering%20bankruptcy%20protection%20in%20May.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGo%20Airlines%20India%20Ltd.'s%20chances%20are%20fading.%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20Kaushik%20Khona%20quit%20at%20the%20end%20of%20November%2C%20saying%20he%20couldn't%20get%20the%20carrier%20flying%20again%20and%20that%20staff%20hadn't%20been%20paid%20for%20six%20months.%20Go%20flight%20attendants%20and%20pilots%20are%20looking%20for%20jobs%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Go%20announced%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20that%20it%20had%20canceled%20all%20scheduled%20flights%20until%20Feb.%204%2C%20extending%20a%20grounding%20that%20began%20in%20May.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Go%20collapses%20for%20good%2C%20it%20would%20be%20the%2012th%20Indian%20airline%20to%20do%20so%20this%20century%2C%20despite%20all%20having%20a%20vast%20and%20increasingly%20mobile%20population%20at%20their%20door.%20Go's%20backers%20spoke%20of%20the%20challenge%20of%20operating%20with%20prohibitively%20high%20costs%2C%20particularly%20on%20fuel%2C%20and%20simultaneously%20needing%20to%20offer%20cut-price%20fares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EDue%20to%20operational%20reasons%2C%20Go%20First%20flights%20until%2004th%20February%202024%20are%20cancelled.%20We%20apologise%20for%20the%20inconvenience%20caused%20and%20request%20customers%20to%20visit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFdMt1cRjeD%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFdMt1cRjeD%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20information.%20For%20any%20queries%20or%20concerns%2C%20please%20feel%20free%20to%20contact%20us.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fw6b3vM4Xsj%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fw6b3vM4Xsj%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20GO%20FIRST%20(%40GoFirstairways)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGoFirstairways%2Fstatus%2F1735519500563288153%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2015%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJindal%20Power%20Ltd.%20-%20Go's%20sole%20potential%20buyer%20under%20its%20insolvency%20resolution%20process%20-%20has%20decided%20not%20to%20bid.%20Local%20media%20reported%20that%20Jindal%20couldn't%20assess%20Go's%20value%20because%20it%20is%20unclear%20how%20many%20planes%20it%20will%20have%2C%20after%20the%20aviation%20regulator%20signaled%20its%20aircraft%20should%20be%20returned%20to%20lessors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGo%2C%20which%20has%2054%20Airbus%20SE%20A320neos%20stuck%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20Jindal%20also%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Next%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGo's%20creditors%2C%20including%20state-run%20Central%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20and%20Deutsche%20Bank%20AG%2C%20may%20sell%20assets%20in%20a%20piecemeal%20fashion%2C%20said%20Sandeep%20Bajaj%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20represented%20some%20operational%20creditors%20in%20the%20insolvency%20case%20of%20Jet%20Airways%20India%20Ltd.%20Go%20owed%20about%2065%20billion%20rupees%20(%24780%20million)%20to%20financial%20creditors%20as%20of%20April%20and%20its%20total%20liabilities%20were%20115%20billion%20rupees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20resolution%20process%20isn't%20going%20anywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bajaj.%20%26quot%3BThe%20company%20is%20already%20at%20a%20stage%20where%20liquidation%20is%20required%26quot%3B%20because%20closed%20businesses%20can%20rarely%20be%20revived%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrounded%20airlines%20can%20lose%20landing%20and%20parking%20slots%2C%20staff%2C%20planes%2C%20licenses%20and%20International%20Air%20Transport%20Association-assigned%20codes%20used%20for%20schedules%20and%20ticketing%2C%20said%20Harsh%20Vardhan%2C%20chairman%20of%20New%20Delhi-based%20Starair%20Consulting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20owners%20need%20to%20clear%20pending%20dues%2C%20including%20to%20travel%20agents%2C%20passengers%2C%20equipment%20suppliers%20and%20staff%2C%20Mr%20Vardhan%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20it%20getting%20revived.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Lure%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20biggest%20two%20carriers%2C%20IndiGo%20and%20a%20rejuvenated%20Air%20India%20Ltd.%2C%20are%20tightening%20their%20grip%20with%20a%20combined%20market%20share%20of%2073%25.%20They%20placed%20record%20orders%20for%20more%20than%20900%20new%20aircraft%20from%20Airbus%20and%20Boeing%20Co.%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bloomberg%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Bloomberg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fvkb3gm58_indias-aviation-market-graph-bloomberg_625x300_15_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkasa%20Air%20started%20up%20in%20August%202022%2C%20backed%20by%20another%20billionaire%2C%20Rakesh%20Jhunjhunwala%2C%20who%20died%20that%20same%20month.%20A%20little%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20it%20has%20a%20market%20share%20of%20around%204%25%2C%20carrying%20over%201.5%20million%20passengers%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20others%20have%20struggled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20billionaire%2C%20Vijay%20Mallya%2C%20founded%20Kingfisher%20Airlines%20Ltd.%20in%202003%2C%20but%20it%20stopped%20flying%20in%202012%20under%20debts%20of%2086%20billion%20rupees.%20The%20authorities%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20extradite%20Mallya%20from%20London%20to%20face%20charges%20of%20alleged%20financial%20fraud.%20His%20lawyers%20have%20said%20the%20order%20to%20return%20to%20India%20ignored%20evidence%20and%20misunderstood%20the%20circumstances%20that%20led%20to%20Kingfisher's%20collapse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20India-based%20Air%20Costa%20folded%20in%202017.%20Jet%20Airways%2C%20once%20India's%20second-biggest%20carrier%20and%20previously%20majority%20owned%20by%20former%20billionaire%20Naresh%20Goyal%2C%20has%20been%20struggling%20to%20resuscitate%20itself%20after%20halting%20operations%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDubai-based%20Murari%20Lal%20Jalan%20and%20Florian%20Fritsch%2C%20chairman%20of%20Kalrock%20Capital%20Management%20Ltd.%2C%20said%20in%20September%20they'd%20invested%203.5%20billion%20rupees%20into%20Jet%2C%20fulfilling%20the%20financial%20requirements%20of%20its%20court-approved%20resolution%20plan.%20While%20they%20intend%20to%20restart%20Jet%20next%20year%2C%20the%20airline%20hasn't%20been%20handed%20over%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBack%20to%20Go%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGo%20was%20established%20in%202005%20by%20billionaire%20Nusli%20Wadia's%20Wadia%20Group%2C%20which%20also%20runs%20Britannia%20Industries%20Ltd.%20and%20Bombay%20Dyeing%20and%20Manufacturing%20Co.%20Wadia%20is%20the%20grandson%20of%20Mohammed%20Ali%20Jinnah%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChasing%20market%20share%2C%20Go%20took%20on%20high%20debts%20to%20pay%20aircraft%20leases%2C%20airport%20fees%20and%20salaries%20when%20jets%20were%20grounded%20during%20Covid%2C%20Starair's%20Mr%20Vardhan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20aviation%20industry%20was%20hit%20hard%20by%20the%20pandemic%2C%20with%20at%20least%2068%20airlines%20involved%20in%20bankruptcy%20protection.%20The%20challenge%20of%20operating%20in%20India%20became%20even%20harder%20as%20passenger%20traffic%20more%20than%20halved.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongestion%20in%20supply%20chains%20exacerbated%20troubles%20for%20Go%2C%20which%20has%20said%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20is%20to%20blame%20as%20half%20of%20its%20fleet%20had%20to%20be%20grounded%20while%20awaiting%20parts%20and%20replacement%20engines.%20Pratt%2C%20a%20unit%20of%20RTX%20Corp.%2C%20has%20refuted%20the%20claim.%20IndiGo%20also%20has%20around%2040%20aircraft%20idled%20due%20to%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Go%20failed%20to%20create%20a%20niche%20for%20itself%20or%20a%20reputation%20as%20an%20efficient%20airline%2C%20whereas%20the%20more%20successful%20IndiGo%20is%20renowned%20for%20its%20on-time%20record%20and%20affordable%20fares%2C%20and%20Air%20India%20for%20its%20legacy%2C%20said%20Mr%20Vardhan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20revival%20%26quot%3Bwould've%20happened%20in%20three%20to%20four%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20longer%20it's%20grounded%2C%20the%20more%20impossible%20it%20becomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702630800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fhmlj3n1_go-airlines-bloomberg_625x300_15_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgo-air-troubles-mount-as-billionaire-backed-airline-nears-shut-down-4678673%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Another%20airline%20backed%20by%20a%20billionaire%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20shutting%20down%20for%20good%2C%20having%20tried%20and%20so%20far%20failed%20to%20attract%20a%20savior%20after%20entering%20bankruptcy%20protection%20in%20May.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgo-air-troubles-mount-as-billionaire-backed-airline-nears-shut-down-4678673%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgo-air-troubles-mount-as-billionaire-backed-airline-near